  "prompt": "Do Jains belong to the OBC category?",
  "response": "In India, the classification of communities into categories such as Other Backward Classes (OBC) can vary by state. Jains as a community are not uniformly categorized under OBC across all states. \n\nIn some states, certain Jain sub-groups may be listed under OBC, while in others, they may not be. For example, in Rajasthan, some Jain castes are included in the OBC list, whereas in other states like Gujarat, Jains are generally not categorized as OBC.\n\nTo determine the specific status of Jains in a particular state, it's essential to refer to the state-specific OBC lists maintained by the respective state governments. If you need information about a specific state, please let me know, and I can help you find the relevant details.",
